  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for customizing a typeface when cloning.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` collects the parameters used to customize an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface>
when cloning it via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone*>. You can specify a font
collection index (for TTC files), a color palette index, palette color overrides,
and variation axis design position coordinates.

This is a value type; no disposal is required.

## Examples

```csharp
// Clone a typeface, selecting the second palette and setting weight to 700
var weightCoord = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
{
    Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"),
    Value = 700f,
};
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new ReadOnlySpan<SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate>(new[] { weightCoord }),
};
using SKTypeface cloned = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
